Rating: 2
This looked like it should be pretty tasty BUT using regular soy sauce made it entirely too salty- and I'm usually one who adds salt at the table! I took great efforts to fix it- added water, rice wine vinegar, and white wine to cut the sauce since reducing it concentrates flavor but then went for a cornstarch slurry to thicken as it was way too thin. I think it would be much better over pasta or rice with a crispy veg (snap peas, bok choy, etc), but I'm trying to avoid the carbs. If nothing else, use LOW SODIUM SOY to control the salt!

