Rating: 3
The sweetness of the mirin, the saltiness of the soy, and the savory flavor of the green onions combined to make a flavorful sauce for surprisingly so few ingredients. The flavor was soaked up by the mushrooms, in particular, which were my favorite part of the dish. Used mahi, as no bass was available. Served with sticky rice and stir fried veggies. Without the green onions sprinkled on top, it is a brown and not that attractive looking dish. But, quick, tasty, and low in fat... other than the mirin, had all ingredients on-hand. Might consider thickening the sauce further with a little corn starch so it clings a bit more to the fish... but I will make this dish again.

