Rating: 2
I expected to love this dish, but I found that the flavor was much too mild and bland. The sauce is very thin and its flavor did not penetrate the fish at all. Maybe it's because the mushrooms and scallions "stew" in the liquid instead of sauteeing, or maybe the added water thins out the sauce too much. Regardless, the only flavor in this dish was in the mushrooms, and even they were bland. If I were to make it again, I'd saute the mushrooms and scallions, deglaze the pan with the sauce (without the water), then add the fish back to the pan to absorb the sauce.

Rating: 4
Delicious and easy! I used tilapia fillets instead of bass (tilapia is inexpensive, farm-raised, low to no mercury). This is going to be a regular at our house - even my 4 year old loved it.